values:
I just got off the phone with my mom. She says all the neighbors have been so supportive.. bringing cards and flowers. They all knew her and they're all very kind. I told my mom that my friends have been wonderfully supportive as well.&nbsp;

I asked how Cash and Sawyer are doing, and Mom's voice sunk down to another level of sadness&nbsp;as she told me they're&nbsp;not doing well at all.. they've been all disoriented... they've been growling at each other, they don't know who the alpha-dog is anymore. (For those of u who don't know, we recently adopted Cash from the Brittany-Rescue program, and we're fostering Saywer, but we love him so we'll probably just keep him too). Maggie has just always been there.... they had respect for her, they never took her chair, they never bothered her.&nbsp;Cash would lick 1/2 the plate&nbsp;and move over to let her finish, just like a gentleman. But now..... now they just don't know what to do. They're wandering around her chair, looking up at it, sniffing around. It's like they're confused and don't know where thier sister is..... but on the other hand Mom thinks they know, and they're just sad.

When I heard that, a part me collapsed inside. I can handle my sadness, I can&nbsp;even sort of handle my family's sadness. But the dogs? No,&nbsp; that's&nbsp;something else altogether; that's a recipe for heart-break.&nbsp;

Mom told me more of when she&nbsp;was trying to&nbsp;keep her from having another siezure.... when the lights were dim, when the house was quiet, when&nbsp;Cash and&nbsp;Sawyer were lying close, and when Mom was cradling our frail helpless Maggie in her lap. I can imagine it&nbsp;so clearly, I can see the tears in Mom's eyes as Maggie lay there staring up into them they whole time. Mom said it was like she was saying, "OK Mom, I waited for you to come home, but now it's time for me to go......"

It's like&nbsp;my mom said, "All you want to do is reach out and pet her soft little head...." But we can't anymore. It's a crushing feeling, like dead-weight. My head is heavy, my eyes are blurry,&nbsp;it's dificult to will any muscles to move. Even my fingers feel especially heavy and stiff.. like it's so much&nbsp;extra work to even type this.&nbsp;I'll be ok, but right now I just need to grieve.

I HATE hunger. It's horrible. I can't imagine how awful those poor starving kids&nbsp;you see on TV&nbsp;must feel.&nbsp;I don't know how the homeless handle it.. I just have no clue. They must feel like they're in Hell.&nbsp;

I eat like 2 or 3 times a day if I'm only awake 12 hours. But I'm still hungry. I'm hungry every 4 hours. It's crap..... complete crap. I know it's because I eat small stuff rather than actual meals, but it's still incredibly annoying to be hungry so often. I've been awake for about 12 hours now and I feel horrible......... my head is pounding, I feel like a complete loser, I'm friggin' starving.. but I absolutely positively CANNOT sleep on an empty stomach. I was laying there feeling icky and tired and like I wanna throw up,&nbsp;although&nbsp;pretty comfy in bed.......... the last thing I wanted to do was get up again....... but my stomach...... rumbling and hurting and sickening...... it's a horrible pain....... a seriously terribly horrible pain....... I had 3 choices: an orange, soup, or oatmeal. I'm no good at peeling oranges, and it probly wouldn't do much for hunger anyway. But I was trying to sleep before I got hungry again so I could save the oatmeal for when I got up and the soup for Matt the next time he was hungry. But no.. I can't sleep with my stomach in so much crappy stupid pain. So here I am, waiting for the oatmeal to cool down while I type.&nbsp;

And Emily, thank you again.... thank you so so soooo much!!! Ya know&nbsp;I never thought I'd say this in my lifetime... but... oatmeal&nbsp;is AMAZING.&nbsp;

We have.. ummmm.. probly by now $5 or so. you can buy a 10-pack of ramen with that..... and go to the dollar store to buy ritz crackers.... and I was hoping for a box of flavored oatmeal, but I guess that's out of reach&nbsp;until tuesday when Matt gets paid for that one day he worked last week.&nbsp; We both applied at Karns, and he's out right now with Yvonne job-hunting some more, so it's not like we're not trying. I'm just scared to apply anywhere that I don't know anybody or that I haven't worked at before. I don't know what my problem is, I've always been like this.&nbsp;

I'm like, scraping the side of the container and it tastes like&nbsp;romen and plastic. YUM

I used to have baby dreams over and over and over.. but in all of them I kept forgetting that I was a mother, and when I remembered, I wouldn't remember where I left my baby and I asked Matt if he knew. But as soon as those thoughts came to me, they left just as quickly.&nbsp;

Gradually, I started remembering that I was a mom for longer periods of time.. but I still forgot.

In another dream, I was very pregnant and about to give birth to my baby. I went through the birth rather quickly, but with a lingering uneasy feeling. That's all I remember.

Then I had a breakthrough: I had a baby girl, and I was watching another girl that wasn't mine. However, I KNEW I would forget about them, so I made sure my mom was there too. Sure enough, I did forget about them, but when I remembered later I knew exactly where to find them; upstairs with Mom. She had them safely in their playpen, which I approached. However, I seemed to be more concerned with the one that wasn't mine.

This time when I went through the bloody, squishy birth, I was perfectly fine with it. Then&nbsp;my&nbsp;dream jumped to when it was all over and I was with my baby at an apartment that Matt and I shared. The love I had for my little boy was&nbsp;INDESCRIBABLE,&nbsp;but he didn't have a name yet. He wasn't quite a Riley... actually he seemed like a CJ. But I remember thinking, "But what does 'C' stand for?" Then it came to me.. Caleb. Caleb Jackson. CJ. PERFECT.&nbsp;I put him on the floor so I could run down to the lobby for a minute, but before I got 2 steps down the stairs I realized all the harm that could be done and rushed back through the door. I was overwhelmed with relief when he was safe and sound in my arms.&nbsp;

The setback dream: I was pregnant but something was horribly wrong.. the baby was creating a small but defined lump in my stomach. I was wondering around a hospital but nomatter where I went or how much I asked, NOBODY would help me! It was so entirely horrible, and I had a heartbreaking miscarraige.

In the dream after that, I was given a darker-skinned baby to foster straight from the hospital. But as I held him in my arms and stared down at the little darling, I knew he was mine because I loved him as I'd love my own. I had a hard time thinking of a name for him.. He wasn't a Riley, he wasn't a Caleb..&nbsp;I think I settled on something, but honestly I can't remember what it was now. All I remember is holding him in my arms in front of me and smiling down at this adorable child who I was destined to protect.

So last night I had another baby dream. I was babysitting this little bundle of smiles.. her name was Analicia. We were on an open&nbsp;moving train to a fun destination, and I made sure to keep this precious little angel in my arms at all times.&nbsp;The other moms were letting their toddlers run around freely and weren't always paying attention, which appalled me beyond belief. I even found myself reaching out to catch them when they stumbled. Meanwhile, I cradled Analicia perfectly with her head on my shoulder. When the train stopped, there was plenty of food available. I was pretty hungry so I started to hand her to my mom, but saw that she only had one hand. She probably could have handled it, but to be safe I decided to keep the baby until my mom was done eating. I GAVE UP FOOD FOR THIS CHILD. I loved her with all my heart.&nbsp;



And yet again, I'm watching the Discovery Health channel while tasting&nbsp;liquid salt as it runs down my cheek.&nbsp;So many concerns, so much to do before the time is right, but that does not stop this feeling. My thoughts are only for my yet-to-be-concieved child. I'm bursting with love and unbridled emotion, and it's SO hard to contain!

I don't want anybody dead. I just want them to go away. I'm sick of people making me angry. I'm tired, I'm hungry, I'm cranky, and I can't be happy about my boyfriend having to&nbsp;run all over the globe when he's about to fall over. He could have hallucinated and swerved off the road.. something&nbsp;could have ran in front of&nbsp;the&nbsp;car..&nbsp;he could have hit something.. just.. just.. so many things could happen on a windy narrow country road in the dark... so many horrible dangerous things.. I worry every day when he does it, but when he's falling asleep?&nbsp;And being told things.. things that I don't agree with, things that I PERSONALLY know are not true, or are true, just something that I don't agree with and is it really that hard to just accept&nbsp;what&nbsp;I'm saying? I don't wanna feel wrong anymore, I don't wanna feel like everything I do or say is wrong. I don't wanna explain myself anymore, I just don't want to be angry anymore.&nbsp; 

I can't wait 'till I get my light-hearted mood back. Anything goes.. is there something wrong? OH I didn't notice 'cuz everything's coooool. Just chillin' like a villan! HARHAR! Problems? WHAT problems??? No problems here! I'm happy slappy and gay. Yay! If you're not happy it's ok cuz i'll tip-toe around you and make sure I help you in any way I can. And I'll be happy doing it because that's who I am.. I care about people, and I love to help. I want to help everyone, and if you're not happy, I'M not happy, because I'm an empath and I can feel what you're feeling and I can understand why you're angry or sad and I don't get angry about it because I'm a calm happy&nbsp;soothing person. I'll take care of you and do anything for you because that's what friends do, no questions asked. I know you'd do the same for me. And if you wouldn't, that's ok because maybe you just need a friend to show you that everything doesn't suck. Because it IS ok! I'm happy, I have energy, I want to go for a walk and I want to go to work and make money to feed us and assist us in doing fun things! We'll be able to spend, but not too much because I'm saving it for my not-yet-concieved baby. I just want the best for him/her, and I'll endure any kind of annoyances with a smile.... a REAL smile.. because my baby is more important to me than any kind of annoyances I have to deal with in the present. I love this child, and I love Matt, and I love my friends and I love my family and I love my boyfriend's family nomatter what they did in the past because God loves EVERYONE and Jesus has allowed me to love everyone as He loves everyone. I'm nice like He is, I'm kind like He is, I care like He does, I don't get angry because He doesn't,&nbsp;I'm gentle like He is, and I love like He does; completely unconditional. Because you know.... I'm just a very happy person!&nbsp;

STAY TUNED for the personality switch of a lifetime. Normality.. COMING SOON to a Jodi near YOU!!!

I've been trying to re-train my brain to type grammatically correct and stuff because I REALLY want to go back to school!!! I think I've been doing a decent job of that, but just for tonight, I think I'll drop it.&nbsp;

It's 4:15 and I should be asleep. Matt is. Oh yeah, and Jasper just puked 3 times in the last 15 minutes. ope, nevermind, 4. are we gonna make it 5? waiting... waiting... ok maybe he's done. OMG i'm so grossed out right now.&nbsp;I mean it's gross to begin with, but when i hear him and i glance over out of sheer impulse he just looks so helpless and convulsing.. and then i think about how that feels, like the morning after vodka and pure sugar. EEAAEAEAEAKKKKKH!!!!

I'm feeling very overwhelmed again. This is not an angry week.. it's just a cluttered week. like head-clutter, I guess. I don't know what to say about it.. I mean stuff will just freak me out, like stuff I don't know how to deal with, and i'll feel like, a&nbsp;silent freaked-out feeling,&nbsp;and then i'll just kinda shut down, and Matt won't understand at first and I'm soooo sick of saying the same damned thing over and over and over and OVER... So I just kinda sit there and not know what to say or how to react or what to do or what to explain. I feel like such a moron but I really don't wanna sit here and try to put the jumbleness into words, it's just so... um.. hmm. well it's something I don't know how to do. Well, unless I just tell him, "I can't find the words, because, you know.. that thing.. that thing that's been happening to my head lately.. I said it yesterday.. and the day before... sort of.. or something." And then I just hope he gets it. But I don't know how anybody could, not even the ever-so talented center of my affection.&nbsp;

I had some good days.. I even had a good week.. it was when I was reunited with Melody. Matt noticed too.. I'd been draggin' butt and then Mom called me to tell me that Melody was at Jubilee Day and then we met up and I'd been SUPER HAPPY ever since! I mean that WHOLE WEEK! I was all too happy to help her with whatever she needed help with, and I actually had energy, I wanted to excercise, I wanted to run up and down steps and I wanted to go kayaking and take walks and stuff.. My muscles DID NOT ACHE!!!!! It was SOOOOO AMAZING!!!!&nbsp;I even found the strengh and calmness to QUIT SMOKING!!!!!!!!!

And then she left. less than a week later, i started not waking up again. i started not sleeping agian. i started getting angry again, and feeling overwhelmed and then when i tried to use that stair-stepper she got me, my knees ached soooo much worse and my muscles generally didn't want to exsert their muscle-strengh. It's like all that endurence and energy I was blessed with the week before just VANISHED.

&nbsp;I was discussing it with Matt, and I was telling him that I'm soooo glad that God allowed the week before Melody left to be a "good week". but then i was thinking that maybe it was a "good week" b/c seeing my long-lost friend made me really happy, and the genuine happiness made the tiredness and the achyness and the spazziness go away. so then it would be a scientific thing. but then Matt said EXACTLY what was running through my mind, "Who's to say that it wasn't God's plan for you to be happy and having a good week when you saw your friend?" And I'm just like "YEAH.. cuz it's an act of God that can also be explained by science, and it's that how the world works?" He agreed.&nbsp;

Other happy things that ease psychoticness:&nbsp;

Kayaking with Adam was purely lovely, and I wanna do it again soooo bad. I hope next time it'll be with my lover. &lt;3

Gettin drunkalunka with Emily and Emily and Peterson at Emily's house.. LOL.. Dancin' to Tori Amos in the middle of the room.. lotsa smileyness!

Partying with Adam and Emily and Emily and Peterson... that was like the most fun night EVER and we have a zillion pics to proove it!!!

Goin' to the music fest with Sue and Ben.. they were kind enough to swoop me up and take me to a far-away land with music and groovin and outdoors and then after dark they bought pitchers so I got loosened up to finally go and dance in the crowd with the live band at Tom Sawyers.. it was AMAZINGLY FUN... I didn't want to stop!!! Then Dukes.. another pitcher &amp; a BEAUTIFUL deck on the water.. OMG it was sooo lovely.. then.. oh THEN! They were tripple-quadrupley kind, picking up Matt and taking us to the diner. I just can't thank them enough.. I hope that I can return the favor somethime REALLY SOON!!!!

A walk to the park and to 7-11 and back with Joe &amp; chattin was really nice

Bein' surprised by my sister and her boyfriend coming early to take us to the music fest today

Even though I dragged Matt ALLLL around the Beach Boys thing, and we were all hot and sweaty, I had a fabulous time just cruzin' up &amp; down front street with the man of my dreams.. then finally meeting up with Joe &amp; Tasha &amp; George on the bridge for the Works.. They were quite magnificent as well!&nbsp;

speaking of "magnificent"... that reminds me of when Matt &amp; I were sitting outside of 7-11over 9 months ago... I don't remember why, but he looked to the side and up at me through his samson-like hair and deep, calming, gentle eyes, reached up to push a lock of hair away from my face with the gentlest touch I've ever felt, and told me, "You.. are magnificent." I knew he meant it with all the love and kindness in his heart and soul...&nbsp;I melted.. I just melted.&nbsp;

I LOVE YOU, MATTHEW!!! &lt;333

I've stopped being a biartch!&nbsp; I haven't been angry in like a week!!! Does this mean that&nbsp;my hormones are getting back to normal??? A LOT of&nbsp;the symptoms are letting up.... I got a little tiny visit for 2 days (first time in LOTSA months), I'm not as tired, I can wake up earlier easier, I can fall asleep earlier easier, my hair isn't as dry as it's been, I have a (somewhat) higher sex drive lately, haven't had any panic or anxiety issues lately.

However, It doesn't seem like i'm losing any weight, I still have a hard time handlign heat, still gettin headaches, still thirsty, still have dry skin, and i'm DEFINITELY still retaining fluid.&nbsp;

I don't know what all of this means. When I try to think, "hmmmm maybe everything will go away on it's own!" someone tells me, "no Jodi, it won't go away, you have to get it fixed.&nbsp;Which is ok.. I have an appointment.&nbsp;

I got to hang out with Melody yesterday for the first time in YEARS! I was so excited, and I feel like a dork saying that, but it's true. But hey, wouldn't YOU be excited to see YOUR friend if you hadn't seen her in a long time? I helped her pack her kitchen stuff. I threw some stuff around but we got like 5 boxes done. It doesn't seem like a lot, but trust me, it took a looooong time!

I really wanna see her and Adam today, but Matt wants me to go to Wally Werld right now and Melody has to clean things b/c someone's going there at 6 to see the place and then she has to pick her hubby up at 8 and I haven't even called Adamus yet. I'm really hot. Which is why we're going to get a fuse and get the air-conditioner running again. LATR
